## §1 Terminal goal — real-semantics formal closure of 4 F-CL-FORMAL axes

The lean4 mechanical layer at `~/core/hexa-meta/formal/lean4/`
proves 4 closure-machinery theorems over hexa-bio's WEAVE composition.

| Axis | Theorem name | Statement | Status (2026-05-12 cycle-30) |
|------|--------------|-----------|---------------|
| F-CL-FORMAL-1 | `sigma_lattice_card` | `sigma 6 = 12` | **REAL-SEMANTICS PROVEN** (`sigma` is a computable Nat divisor-sum; `rfl`) |
| F-CL-FORMAL-2 | `landauer_monotonic` | `heatConsumed (compose s₁ s₂) ≥ max …` | ✅ **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v2** (2026-05-12 cycle-30+++, hexa-meta `2c68bea`) — `Strategy` heat field promoted `Nat` (integer kT·ln2 quanta) → `ℝ` (joules); `LandauerPass s := s.heat ≥ s.bits_erased · landauerFloorPerBit` where `landauerFloorPerBit = kT · Real.log 2` (Mathlib-backed). `ComposeMode {seq | merge}`: sequential is heat-additive, merge is sub-additive with explicit `cancel` parameter. `compose := composeWith .seq` (backward-compat). Bonus theorems: `landauer_pass_compose` (closure under .seq), `landauer_pass_merge` (closure under .merge with `cancel ≤ b₁+b₂`), `landauer_pass_heat_nonneg`. v3 stretch: `[Fact (0 < kT)]` parametrisation + cancellation derived from underlying WEAVE algebra. |
| F-CL-FORMAL-3 | `pi_p2_verifier_terminates` | `∃ n, verifierSteps q ≤ n` | ✅ **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v2** (2026-05-12 cycle-30+++, hexa-meta `2c68bea`) — `verifierSteps q := c.size * 2 ^ q.depth + q.payload` (exponential-in-depth; matches literature-standard Π^p_2 worst case = 2^d nested quantifier-elimination branches). Witness `n = 12 * 2 ^ q.depth + q.payload`. Bonus: `verifierSteps_mono_depth` (monotone in depth + payload), `two_pow_pos`. v3 stretch: recursive verifier function with `WellFoundedRelation` termination proof, not just a closed-form upper bound. |
| F-CL-FORMAL-4 | `closure_cert_idempotent` | `discloseTwice c = discloseOnce c` | ✅ **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v2** (2026-05-12 cycle-30++) — `ClosureCert` now carries `caveat_bag` / `signer_set` (Mathlib `Finset Nat`) + `seal_caveats` / `seal_signers` snapshots; `discloseOnce` is a seal-on-first-disclosure operation (idempotent by `if_pos` on the `disclosed` flag). Bonus theorems: `caveat_bag_invariant`, `signer_set_invariant`, `addCaveat_idempotent`, `signer_set_monotonic` all kernel-checked. Mathlib SHA `f8e537424d154a7eaa025c4abab16c96c626f2e0` pinned via `lake-manifest.json`. v3 cycle-30+++ remains: polymorphic carrier (`[DecidableEq α]` instead of `Nat` for caveat/signer IDs). |

**v1 → v2 promotion DoD per axis** (cycle-30++): full WEAVE composition
algebra (sub-additive composition under reversible re-merge; real-valued
heat with `Real.log` + Mathlib SHA-pin; exponential-in-depth Π^p_2 worst
case; payload-level disclosure invariants) + Mathlib-backed proof bodies
+ sorry-count = 0 + machine-checked under `lake build`. The v1 → v2 work
is **NOT a v1.x closure blocker** — by design, the v1.x cert surrogate
is the `raw_91_c3_disclose:MVP_caveat` disclosure (per `.roadmap.weave`
line 21), and v1 PASS is the maximum formal-axis closure available in
the v1.x track.

