## §4 raw_91 honest C3 disclosure

**As of 2026-05-12 (cycle 30+++):**
- Axis 1 is REAL-SEMANTICS PROVEN: `sigma 6 = 12` holds genuinely
  against the computable Nat divisor-sum definition.
- Axes 2/3/4 are **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v2**: the lean4
  statements typecheck and the proof bodies kernel-check against the
  upgraded semantics — `Strategy {bits_erased : Nat, heat : ℝ}` with
  real Landauer floor `kT · Real.log 2` and `ComposeMode {seq | merge}`
  (axis 2); exponential-in-depth `verifierSteps q := c.size * 2 ^ q.depth
  + q.payload` matching Π^p_2 literature-standard worst case (axis 3);
  `ClosureCert` with `Finset Nat` caveat-bag + signer-set + seal-on-
  disclosure snapshots (axis 4). All 4 axes sorry-count=0, kernel-checked
  on lean4 v4.30.0-rc2 + Mathlib SHA `f8e537424d154a7eaa025c4abab16c96c626f2e0`
  via `lake build N6` → 1919/1919 jobs PASS.
- **PASS = sorry-free against WEAVE-semantics v2**, NOT against a fully
  polymorphic / algebra-derived / recursive-verifier formulation. v3
  semantics (`[Fact (0 < kT)]` parametrised temperature, recursive
  verifier with `WellFoundedRelation` termination, polymorphic
  `[DecidableEq α]` disclosure carrier) is the cycle-30++++ stretch —
  see §3. v3 is **NOT a v1.x closure blocker NOR a v2.0.0 cert-strength
  deliverable**.
- **The v2 PASS state EXCEEDS the v1.x track terminal** for the formal
  axes (per `.roadmap.weave` line 21: v1.x uses the
  `raw_91_c3_disclose:MVP_caveat` disclosure as the cert surrogate; full
